article.description: — Jordan King scored 19 points, David Sloan had a double-double and all the East Tennessee State starters scored in double figures in the Buccaneers' 88-85 victory over Samford on Saturday.
article.headline: King, Sloan lead ETSU over Samford 88-85
article.linkText: King, Sloan lead ETSU over Samford 88-85
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- — Jordan King scored 19 points, David Sloan had a double-double and all the East Tennessee State starters scored in double figures in the Buccaneers' 88-85 victory over Samford on Saturday. Sloan had 12 points and 10 rebounds for ETSU (11-8, 3-3 Southern Conference). Ledarrius Brewer added 17 points, Ty Brewer 15 and Jaden Seymour 10. King and Brewer had five 3-pointers apiece. Sloan made 1 of 2 free throws with 4.6 seconds left for a three-point lead before Samford's Cooper Kaifes missed a 3-point attempt. All the starters for the Bulldogs (11-6, 1-4) were also in double figures. Logan Dye and Jaden Campbell scored 20 points each, Wesley Cardet added 15, Ques Glover 12 and Kaifes 10. Campbell had six 3-pointers. ----
